# ScyllaDB Cloud Provider (Vetric Fork)

The ScyllaDB Cloud provider enables you to manage [ScyllaDB Cloud](https://cloud.scylladb.com/) resources using Terraform. ScyllaDB Cloud is a fully managed database-as-a-service built on [ScyllaDB](https://www.scylladb.com/), a high-performance NoSQL database compatible with Apache Cassandra and Amazon DynamoDB.

> **Note:** This is the [Vetric fork](https://github.com/vetric-io/terraform-provider-scylladbcloud) with additional features. For the official provider, see [scylladb/terraform-provider-scylladbcloud](https://github.com/scylladb/terraform-provider-scylladbcloud).

Use this provider to:
- Create and manage ScyllaDB Cloud clusters on AWS or GCP
- Configure VPC peering and network connectivity
- Manage IP allowlist rules for cluster access
- Retrieve connection credentials for your applications

## Getting Started

### Authentication

Before using this provider, you must obtain an API token from ScyllaDB Cloud. See [Obtaining an API Key](https://cloud.docs.scylladb.com/stable/api-docs/api-get-started.html#obtaining-an-api-key-beta) for instructions.

-> **Security Tip:** Never commit your API token to version control. Use environment variables or a secrets management system.

### Installation

This provider is distributed via GitHub releases. Download the appropriate binary for your platform from [GitHub Releases](https://github.com/vetric-io/terraform-provider-scylladbcloud/releases) and install it:

```bash
# Create the plugins directory
mkdir -p ~/.terraform.d/plugins/github.com/vetric-io/terraform-provider-scylladbcloud/0.0.1/$(uname -s | tr '[:upper:]' '[:lower:]')_$(uname -m)/

# Move the provider binary (adjust version as needed)
mv terraform-provider-scylladbcloud ~/.terraform.d/plugins/github.com/vetric-io/terraform-provider-scylladbcloud/0.0.1/$(uname -s | tr '[:upper:]' '[:lower:]')_$(uname -m)/
```

Then add the provider to your Terraform configuration:

```terraform
terraform {
  required_providers {
    scylladbcloud = {
      source = "github.com/vetric-io/terraform-provider-scylladbcloud"
    }
  }
}
```

